Key Match Events: Abdoulaye Seck headed home a Krepin Diatta free-kick to give Senegal a deserved lead shortly past the hour mark.
Sadio Mane missed a huge chance and also saw a goal chalked off for offside.
Mane turned provider for substitute Iliman Ndiaye to wrap up the victory on the cusp of stoppage time.
Morgan Guilavogui's volley was well saved by Edouard Mendy in stoppage time.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Senegal confirmed their spot as Group C winners and maintained their 100 per cent record in defence of their first title from 2021.
Guinea will advance with four points as one of the four best third-place group finishers at the tournament.
Cameroon's dramatic late win over The Gambia in Bouake affected Guinea's standing in the group.
